  "prompt": "Can someone get pregnant 10 days after their period?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to get pregnant 10 days after a period, depending on the timing of ovulation and the lifespan of sperm. Typically, ovulation occurs about 14 days before the start of the next period in a standard 28-day cycle. If you have a cycle that is longer or shorter than 28 days, ovulation may occur earlier or later. Sperm can live in a woman's reproductive tract for up to 5 days, so if you have intercourse in the days leading up to ovulation, there is a chance of becoming pregnant. Therefore, if a woman has a shorter menstrual cycle, ovulation could occur around the time when she might have intercourse 10 days after her last period. \n\nIf pregnancy is a concern or if you're trying to conceive, tracking your menstrual cycle and ovulation can provide more clarity.",
